snippet.textDisplay: I think it’s interesting that he’s quoted as saying, “what if I pulled your hair *back*?” Using “back” like this seems to imply returning an action (Ex. “hit back,” or “kiss back.”). I wonder if maybe she pulled his hair, and he was trying to flip it back on her, to establish how unacceptable that behaviour is, and trying to point out that she can’t do something like that just because she’s a woman. I feel like a threat wouldn’t be phrased like that. Just a thought, though.
